RoleDescription:
The Senior Electrified Controls Development Engineer is responsible for designing control algorithms for embedded vehicle systems capable of combine the electric and thermal energy in order to achieve the most optimized operating point of a vehicle in terms of fuel consumption and emissions.The Senior engineer will be able to assess the best solution and tool to be applied for each situation during the development process and also needs to be prepared to apply problem solving skills in case of issue detection and software debugging.

 Be able to work independently with a cross functional team(systems and software) to develop new controls features;
 Interface with systems and calibration to fully understand the requirements.
 Develop implementation strategies.
 Assess and document the impacts against regulatory requirement;
 Markup models to ensure the design meets functional/operational requirements;
 Validate the design during the production process;
 Collaborate across multiple CoE's supporting global product development;
 Track their progress and report status to management with escalation of issues/risks;
 Present feature overviews to other controls engineers or calibration teams.Bachelor of Science in Mechanical, Mechatronic or Electrical Engineering, or related Engineering field.Controls Background  A solid foundation in classical controls, including transfer functions, PID control, and open/closed-loop systems. Advanced control applications would be a preferred qualification.Fundamental Vehicle Knowledge  Familiarity with powertrain systems or, at a minimum, experience with simulations involving rotational body dynamics.Domain Expertise  Depth in a specific technical area relevant to powertrain torque control. For an extreme example, a candidate working on a masters or PhD project in wind turbine controls could be a potential fit due to the overlap in rotational dynamics and electrical power control.Tool Proficiency  Proficiency in MATLAB and Simulink is essential.Knowledge on automotive hybrid and electric vehiclesKnowledge in control and automation
